# Type Strictness (Frontend + Backend)

Types must be **explicit, shared, and identical** across client and server. `strict: true` in `tsconfig.json` is the floor — not the ceiling.

## Single source of truth

| Layer | Location | Use for |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Domain entities | `src/types/index.ts` | Customer, Agent, Message, Role, etc. |
| Input / API payloads | `src/lib/schemas/*.ts` | Zod schema + `z.infer<typeof schema>` |
| Server responses | Same schema or `types` | Never hand-written duplicate interfaces |

```tsx
// ✅ One schema → validation + types
export const customerCreateSchema = z.object({ name: z.string().min(1), phone: z.string().min(10) });
export type CustomerCreateInput = z.infer<typeof customerCreateSchema>;

// ✅ Domain entity stays in types/
import type { Customer } from "@/types";
```

When backend/API exists: server handler input/output types **must** come from the same Zod schema or `@/types` — not a parallel `interface ApiCustomer`.

## Forbidden

| Pattern | Why |
|---------|-----|
| `any` | Never in new code; replace when touching legacy |
| `as any` / `as unknown as Foo` | Bypasses safety — parse with Zod first |
| `@ts-ignore` / `@ts-expect-error` | Fix the type error instead |
| Duplicate interfaces | e.g. `CustomerDTO` mirroring `Customer` with different optional fields |
| `Record<string, any>` | Use `Record<string, unknown>` + narrow, or a typed map |
| Optional everything `?` | Only when field is genuinely optional in domain |
| `enum` duplicates | Use `Role`, `RFMSegment` unions from `@/types` |
| Untyped `fetch` JSON | `const data = await res.json()` — parse with schema |

## Allowed narrow exceptions

- Third-party chart/tooltip callbacks where lib types are weak — cast **once** at boundary with a comment why.
- `routeTree.gen.ts` — generated; do not edit.
- **Legacy code** with `as any` (Select `onValueChange`, `cadence.ts`) — do not add new ones; replace with proper union when you touch that file.

## Backend ↔ frontend parity checklist

- [ ] Request body type = `z.infer` of shared schema
- [ ] Response shape matches what frontend store/hooks expect (`Customer`, not loose object)
- [ ] Nullable fields agree (`null` vs `undefined` — prefer optional `?` in types, document in schema)
- [ ] Enum/string unions identical (`OrderStatus`, `AuditAction`)
- [ ] Changing a field in `@/types` → grep all usages + update seed + store + UI

## Store actions

```tsx
// ❌
addCustomer(c: any)

// ✅
addCustomer(c: Omit<Customer, "id" | "purchases" | ...>)
```

## Do not ship

- Type errors suppressed instead of fixed
- Frontend assumes fields backend doesn't guarantee
- Wider types on frontend "just in case"
